fugees streaming along the roads of occupied France the devastation at Pearl Harbor as photographed by a Navy film unit working for Hollywood director John Ford and the U S  victory over the Japanese at Midway   the decisive sea battle of the Pacific war  Online video system requirements  QuickTime 7 player  or equivalent  More information on this video  http www pbs org perilousfight teachers episodes html  http traveler vmi edu 300k pbs pei000 1 300k mp4 Low resolution video  http traveler vmi edu 800k pbs pei000 1 800k mp4 High resolution video  World War  1939 1945   Personal narratives  American  World War  1939 1945  The perilous fight  America s World War II in color   Episode 2  Battlefronts  1942 1944  electronic resource    co produced by TWI  Carlton   KCTS Seattle written and produced by Scott Pearson  The second episode covers America s early involvement in the war  from the massive buildup of the country s military and industrial capabilities to preparations for D Day  Among the many scenes captured in color footage are the mobilization of women and African Americans on the industrial home front and in the military the internment of Japanese Americans training of African American aviators at Alabama s Tuskegee Institute the horrors of the Warsaw Ghetto and the boarding of troops onto landing craft bound for Normandy  scene of what was to be the largest amphibious invasion in history  Online video system requirements  QuickTime 7 player  or equivalent  More information on this video  http www pbs org perilousfight teachers episodes html  http traveler vmi edu 300k pbs pei000 2 300k mp4 Low resolution video  http traveler vmi edu 800k pbs pei000 2 800k mp4 High resolution video   World War  1939 1945   Personal narratives  American  World War  1939 1945  The perilous fight  America s World War II in color   Episode 3  Wrath  D Day to VE Day  electronic resource    co produced by TWI  Carlton   KCTS Seattle written and produced by Greg Palmer  The third e